12.x.1991
, A. Riedel lgt. ( ZKDC );

subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdominal sternum VII (
Fig. 15
) shallowly emarginate, with narrow, apically rounded and setose median process, projecting from inner side. Sternite VIII (
Figs 16, 17
); paired prongs bifurcate and moderately lobed ventrally near apex. Tergum VII nearly evenly rounded posteriorly. Tergite VIII forming a pair of sclerites, narrowly connected medially, narrowly rounded apically. Apical sclerite of segment IX inconspicuous. Aedeagus (
Fig. 18
); apical portion of tegmen 0.7 times as long as basal-piece, trilobed apically.
